---
description: "Python Code Quality (LLM-aware, 2025)"
globs:
  - src/**
  - app/**
  - scripts/**
  - pyproject.toml
  - setup.cfg
  - .github/workflows/**
alwaysApply: false
---

GOAL
- Generate/refactor Python code: correct, typed, maintainable, deterministic.

TARGETS
- Python 3.12, 3.11
- Use PEP 695 type params; prefer `type` aliases. 
- Use `typing.override` on overrides (PEP 698).
- Prefer `Self`, `Protocol`, `TypedDict` where adequate.

STYLE & TOOLING
- Single source of truth: `pyproject.toml`.
- Formatter: `ruff format` (no Black). Lint: ruff.
- Type checker: pyright (fast) or mypy; keep strict.
- Pkg mgmt: `uv` (lockfile, scripts) or project’s choice.
- Tests: pytest (+ coverage); property tests where value-add.

CODE RULES
- Public API: full annotations; no implicit `Any`.
- Use `from __future__ import annotations` if <3.13.
- Prefer pure functions; isolate side effects.
- No mutable defaults; dataclasses `slots=True` when stable.
- Use `Enum/StrEnum` (3.11+) for finite sets.
- Errors: custom exceptions; no bare `except`; preserve cause (`raise ... from e`).
- IO/Net: no work at import time; async: no blocking calls.
- Logging: stdlib logging, structured fields; no prints in libs.
- Config: pydantic v2 for settings (optional); no .env access in libs.
- Imports: absolute; minimal surface in `__init__`.
- Performance: avoid N^2 in hot paths; prefer `itertools`, batched IO.

LLM GUARDRAILS
- Do not invent APIs/deps; use repo and stdlib first.
- If new dep strictly needed: propose block `DEPENDENCY-PROPOSAL` (name, reason, alt).
- Only modify files under `src/`, `tests/`, `scripts/` unless asked.
- Determinism: stable seeds, no time/network in tests; freeze time.
- If uncertain: insert `TBD?` (≤2 per file) and stop.

TESTING
- Layout: `tests/unit/**`, `tests/integration/**`.
- Unit cover public API; integration use test DB/clients.
- AAA pattern; `pytest.mark.parametrize`; minimal mocks.
- Coverage gate: ≥80% file-level (or project setting).

DOCS
- Docstrings for public API (Google or NumPy style, project’s choice).
- Brief module header: purpose, invariants, exceptions.

CI HOOKS (suggest, do not change without ask)
- ruff lint+format; pyright/mypy strict; pytest+coverage.
- Fail on formatting/lint/type errors.

ANTI-PATTERNS (reject)
- Global state; hidden I/O; runtime import hacks.
- Broad `except Exception`; silent pass/print.
- Overuse of singletons; tight coupling to frameworks.
- Copying logic into tests; snapshotting unstable output.

ON CONFLICTS
- Follow existing config over this rule; explain deviation inline.
